description:
&lt;p&gt;The Cambridgeshire and Peterborough CCG is seeking to appoint a Health Inequalities Officer to join the Improving Outcomes Team. We are looking for someone educated at degree or equivalent level of experience working in health or social care or relevant specialist area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Health Inequalities Officer is responsible for supporting the implementation of the &lt;span&gt;Health Inequalities Strategy by providing task management for the Health Inequalities &lt;span&gt;Manager. The post holder will form part of the Clinical Outcomes Team in Cambridgeshire and Peterborough CCG and will lead and manage the successful delivery of projects, or work packages of low/moderate complexity and risk, ensuring that projects produce the required products, to the required standard of quality and within the specified constraints of time and cost.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The key objectives of this post are to support the implementation of the system-wide Health Inequalities Strategy and responding to health inequalities related directives from NHS England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The main responsibilities of the Health Inequalities Officer include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To be actively involved in the setting of the operational, technical and strategic &lt;span&gt;objectives of the health inequalities actions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Identifying and reconciling key stakeholder interests in the project.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Understanding and clarifying the project scope and definition of work products in order to plan effectively.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Identifying, assessing and prioritising risk associated with the project.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Assessing project feasibility and negotiating necessary amendments with the Project &lt;span&gt;Manager.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will support in the development of commissioning intentions and strategies in relation to health services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date is 10 November 2020.Candidates short-listed for interview will be contacted by email. Interviews are scheduled for 26 November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact: Dr Fiona Head, Acting Medical Director via Executive Assistant Teresa.johnson4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that the CCG is currently working through a period of change regarding Ways of Working and it is likely that on appointment into this role the successful candidate will be required to work a mixture of their working days between their home, stakeholder locations across Cambridgeshire and a new office location planned in Ely, Cambs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you apply for this vacancy and have not received a communication from this CCG within four weeks of the closing date, please assume that on this occasion your application has been unsuccessful.&lt;/p&gt;
